      propertyPath: scatterer
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 7002285934860079271}
    - target: {fileID: 5109087311396199045, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: selectionCollider
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 7369253916546511961}
    - target: {fileID: 5122842465899161861, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "The Crocus's Soliloquy\n\nDown in my solitude under the snow, \nWhere
        nothing cheering can reach me; \nHere, without light to see how to grow,
        \nI'll trust to nature to teach me. \nSoon as the frost will get out of my
        bed, \nFrom this cold dungeon to free me \n,I will peer up with my little
        bright head; \nAll will be joyful to see me. \nMany, perhaps, from so simple
        a flower \nThis little lesson may borrow \u2014 \nPatient to-day, through
        its gloomiest hour, \nWe come out the brighter to-morrow.\n\n\u2014 Hannah
        Flagg Gould"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5122842465899161861, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5431834928911583797, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 7d1a11bb9dbdf454f8f737e009c4bdaa, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 5902464882853280731, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: instanceId
      value: a8485130-377b-48db-ab26-a191b6c3a0c1
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082416, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "## Frances Allen Harper \u2014 The Crocuses (excerpt)\n\nNot a daffodil
        nor daisy\nHad dared to raise its head;\nNot a fairhaired dandelion\nPeeped
        timid from its bed;\n\nThough a tremor of the winter\nDid shivering through
        them run;\nYet they lifted up their foreheads\nTo greet the vernal sun.\n\nAnd
        the sunbeams gave them welcome,\nAs did the morning air\u2014\nAnd scattered
        o\u2019er their simple robes\nRich tints of beauty rare.\n\nSoon a host of
        lovely flowers\nFrom vales and woodland burst;\nBut in all that fair procession\nThe
        crocuses were first."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082416, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 6181259333930047258, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: GsplatAsset
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 4599839170941234424, guid: aeb8cb6e35704c046904a722b0511c05, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 6181259333930047258, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_assetGuid
      value: aeb8cb6e35704c046904a722b0511c05
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 6835627233580907840, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 4b185898bdecf7a4f93c56d71cddf77d, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 7173199714940506848, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: '## Crocus, Greek Mythology

        Crocus was a young mortal, who
        was in love with the Nymph Smilax. Either the love was not returned, or no
        love was possible between mortal and nymph, leading to the gods taking pity
        upon Crocus, turning him into the saffron flower as a relief for his grief.'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 7173199714940506848, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 7417057368276200879, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 580d7a2aafce14e4995172aa5ad52cf3, type: 3}
